    <h2>Modern Systems for Modern Living</h2>
    <p>Behind every comfortable home and efficient workplace lies a network of carefully designed and installed systems — plumbing, heating, ventilation and sanitary installations that work seamlessly, silently and reliably. At SAM Construction, our technical installations division delivers these essential systems with the precision and forward-thinking design that Luxembourg's high standards demand.</p>
    <p>Whether you are building new, renovating or upgrading existing systems, we design and install solutions that prioritise comfort, energy efficiency and long-term reliability — all in full compliance with Luxembourg's technical regulations.</p>

    <h3>Our Sanitary &amp; Systems Services</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Complete plumbing installations — hot and cold water distribution, waste systems</li>
      <li>Bathroom and kitchen sanitary fitting</li>
      <li>Central heating systems — condensing boilers, heat pumps, underfloor heating</li>
      <li>Domestic hot water systems including solar thermal integration</li>
      <li>Mechanical ventilation with heat recovery (VMC double flux)</li>
      <li>Rainwater harvesting and greywater recycling systems</li>
      <li>Gas installations (by certified partners)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Energy Efficiency at the Core</h3>
    <p>Luxembourg's energy performance regulations (Règlement Grand-Ducal on energy performance) set demanding targets for heating systems, hot water production and ventilation. Our installations are designed to meet or exceed these requirements, helping achieve the energy efficiency class needed for building certification and eligibility for PRIMe House subsidies.</p>
    <p>We specify high-efficiency components — condensing boilers with seasonal efficiencies above 95%, air-source and ground-source heat pumps with COP ratings above 4.0, and heat recovery ventilation systems that recover over 90% of exhaust air energy. These specifications translate directly into lower energy bills and reduced environmental impact for our clients.</p>

    <h3>Smart Home Integration</h3>
    <p>Modern sanitary and heating systems increasingly interface with smart home controls. We install and configure programmable thermostats, zone control systems and remote monitoring solutions that allow homeowners to manage their comfort and energy use from anywhere. Integration with KNX home automation platforms is available for clients seeking the highest level of control.</p>

    <h3>Compliance &amp; Certification</h3>
    <p>All our installations comply with Luxembourg's technical regulations, including the prescriptions of the Administration de la Gestion de l'Eau for plumbing works and the Inspection du Travail et des Mines (ITM) for heating and gas installations. We coordinate all required inspections and provide complete technical documentation for building permit compliance and energy passport certification.</p>

    <h3>Maintenance &amp; Aftercare</h3>
    <p>A well-maintained system lasts longer and performs better. We offer guidance on maintenance schedules and can coordinate annual servicing of heating systems, ventilation filters and plumbing inspections. Our handover documentation includes detailed system schematics, equipment manuals and maintenance checklists.</p>
